	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Grandfather of the jurist, perhaps a senator in the mid-second century. Note the contrast implied by Cic. Mur. 16: pater enim fuit equestri loco, avus nulla inlustri laude celebratus. (RS, MS-RP 1.289) His rank as senator, rejected by Nicolet, L'Ordre equestre 1028f., is defended by Shackleton Bailey, Onom.\n" .
